  "body": "```\r\nEIP: 2054\r\nTitle: Add missing cheap unique ID and external call hierarchy introspection\r\nAuthor: CryptoManiacs team: Anton Bukov <k06aaa@gmail.com> and Sergej Kunz <info@deacix.de>\r\nType: Core\r\nCategory: Core\r\nCreated: 2019-05-20\r\nUpdated: 2019-05-20\r\n```\r\n\r\nI would like to avoid this situation and not to use `SSTORE` at all:\r\n\r\n```Solidity\r\nuint nextTaskId = 1;\r\nfunction addTask(Task memory task) public {\r\n    tasks[nextTaskId] = task;\r\n    emit TaskAdded(msg.sender, nextTaskId, task.value);\r\n    nextTaskId++;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI wish to have some kind of unique ID inside function for example to keep some task in mapping:\r\n\r\n```Solidity\r\nfunction addTask(Task memory task) public {\r\n    uint256 key = block.number;\r\n    tasks[key] = task;\r\n    emit TaskAdded(msg.sender, key, task.value);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut several transactions will result a conflict, letâ€™s imagine we even have a `tx.hash`:\r\n\r\n```Solidity\r\nfunction addTask(Task memory task) public {\r\n    uint256 key =tx.hash;\r\n    tasks[key] = task;\r\n    emit TaskAdded(msg.sender, key, task.value);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut this also will not work in case of several calls from a different smart contract, but wait:\r\n\r\n```Solidity\r\nfunction addTask(Task memory task) public {\r\n    uint256 key = keccak256(tx.hash, gasleft());\r\n    tasks[key] = task;\r\n    emit TaskAdded(msg.sender, key, task.value);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut this will not work again in case of implicit gas limit specification for call: `register.addTask.gas(100000)(task)`.\r\n\r\nI wonder if we can introduce new opcode for this, like:\r\n- external calls counter `msg.callnumber`\r\n- external calls path (array of nested subcall counts) `msg.callnumber(i)`\r\n- external calls introspection `getsender(i)`",
